content.description: Climb the longer face to the north of Bankruptcy Wall.
content.protection: All bolts, shares anchor with Out of Pocket to the immediate right.
content.location: About 10 yards and up right from Double Dipping.

content.description: Climb straight up a steep section on good holds.  Pity the climb is not longer.
content.protection: All bolts to a separate anchor.
content.location: The left route of the short climbs facing east.

content.description: Follow the arete on the right side of a small face.
content.protection: All bolts, shares anchor with Payback to the left.

content.description: Climb technical face moves up and right to good holds.  The crux is the bottom.
content.protection: All bolts, shares anchor with CU-Anytime.
content.location: The middle of the short routes facing north.

content.description: The climb has two climbing sections separated by a ledge.  The climb starts on the compact rock, crosses a ledge and goes straight up softer rock to the top.
content.protection: All bolts to anchors and chain at the top.
content.location: This climb is located on the second short cliff to the north of Bankruptcy Wall

content.description: The warmup of the area.  It can be used to set TRs for the routes to the left.
content.protection: All bolts, shares anchor with Insufficient Funds.
content.location: The rightmost of the short routes facing north.

content.description:
Several separate small cliffs to the north and up from Bankruptcy Wall. 

  There are six climbs in this area grouped in three separate sections of rock.  Left to right the climbs follow: 

Double Dipping 5.10- (sport; a climb with a ledge in the middle)   ---------- 

Payback 5.9+ (sport;  climbs next to each other on a face) 

Out of Pocket 5.10- (sport)   ---------- 

Overdrawn 5.10+ (sport;  three shorter climbs to the right of above) 

Insufficient Funds 5.10+ (sport) 

CU-Anytime 5.8 (sport)
